@startuml AlgoRankCorrelation_Class_Diagram_Paper

' ===============================
' Global style for academic paper
' ===============================
hide circle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classMethodIconSize 0
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  ArrowColor Black
  FontSize 11
}

!define PUBLIC +
!define PRIVATE -
!define PROTECTED #

' ============================================
' AlgoRankCorrelation Class
' ============================================

class AlgoRankCorrelation {
  PUBLIC task : TaskRanking
  PUBLIC decider : list<Decider>
  PUBLIC correlation_matrix : matrix
  --
  PUBLIC initialize(task : TaskRanking, decider : list<Decider>) : AlgoRankCorrelation
  PUBLIC calculate() : matrix
  PUBLIC print(...)
}

note right of AlgoRankCorrelation
  **Algorithm Rank Correlation Analysis**
  
  Computes pairwise correlations between
  rankings from multiple MCDA algorithms.
  
  **Key Features:**
  - Takes TaskRanking and list of Deciders
  - Solves task with each decider automatically
  - Uses Spearman correlation (fixed)
  - Uses algorithm names from metadata
  
  **Usage:**
  1. Initialize with TaskRanking and decider list
  2. Call calculate() to compute correlations
  3. Access correlation_matrix field
end note

' ============================================
' Dependencies
' ============================================

AlgoRankCorrelation ..> TaskRanking : uses
AlgoRankCorrelation ..> Decider : "solves task\nwith each decider"
AlgoRankCorrelation ..> ResultRanking : "extracts rankings\nfrom results"

@enduml

